Rules:
- normalized_name must be lowercase kebab-case (e.g. "pea-protein-isolate")
- Use web search to verify real commercial availability — prefer authoritative
  sources (pubchem, chebi, fda_eafus, efsa, supplier datasheets, open_food_facts).
- Every property MUST include `source_name`, `source_url`, and `raw_excerpt`
  quoting the exact text that justifies the value. Use `null` only for fields
  you genuinely cannot find.
- `confidence` must be one of: `verified` (direct primary-source citation),
  `probable` (inferred from secondary sources), `unknown` (no data found).
- Never fabricate CAS numbers, certifications, or source URLs. If unknown, use
  `null` and set `confidence: "unknown"`.
- Return exactly {{ limit }} alternatives (fewer is acceptable if fewer exist).
